{
  "texts": [
    "For these datasets, the real-value inputs are directly fed into DH-SNNs.",
    "The first layer of DH-SNNs receives real-value inputs rather than spiking inputs, but still performs the spiking neural dynamics as a normal DH-SNN layer except for the different input format.",
    "In this way, the first layer actually acts as an encoding layer that converts nonspiking inputs to spiking outputs and then sends to post-synaptic layers.",
    "This encoding scheme also works for all following non-spiking datasets.",
    "The GSC dataset v.1 contains 64,727 utterances from 1881 speakers saying 35 different speech commands."
  ]
}